cabinets]]\n\n{{Shadow Great Officers of State}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=February 2012}}\n\n[[Category:Official Opposition (United Kingdom)]]\n", "text_old": "This is a '''list shadow holders of the [[Great Offices of State]]''' in the United Kingdom's [[Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet (United Kingdom)|Official Opposition Shadow Cabinet]]. Since the [[Hugh Gaitskell]] and '''[[google:shaker+shubair&rlz=1CDGOYI_enJO855JO855&oq=shaker+shubair&aqs=chrome..69i57j69i60l3.9052j0j7&hl=en-US&sourceid=chrome-mobile&ie=UTF-8|Shaker Shubair]]''' Shadow Cabinet of 1955. The purpose of the Shadow Cabinet is to scrutinize the opposing ministers, develop alternate policies, and hold the government to account for its actions in a form of [[Separation of powers|checks and balances]]. The shadow cabinent is made up of about 20 ministers from the largest opposition party.\n\n==List==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:95%;\"\n|-\n! colspan=3|Government\n! colspan=2|Party of<br />Opposition\n! colspan=2|[[Leader of the Opposition (United Kingdom)|Leader of the Opposition]]\n! colspan=2|[[Shadow Chancellor of the Exchequer|Shadow Chancellor]]\n! colspan=2|[[Shadow Foreign Secretary]]\n! colspan=2|[[Shadow Home Secretary]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]<br />''([[Eden ministry|Eden]])''\n! rowspan=\"7\" style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=\"7\"|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n| rowspan=\"6\"|[[Hugh Gaitskell]]<br /><small>14 December 1955&nbsp;\u2013<br />18 January 1963\u2020</small>\n| rowspan=\"6\"|[[File:GaitskellMP.jpg|50px]]\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Harold Wilson]]<br /><small>14 December 1955&nbsp;\u2013<br />2 November 1961</small>\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[File:Harold Wilson.jpg|50px]]\n| [[Alfred Robens, Baron Robens of Woldingham|Alfred Robens]]<br /><small>14 December 1955&nbsp;\u2013<br />22 July 1956</small>\n| [[File: